body:
### Describe the bug

Over in pandas when building our manylinux and musllinux wheels with Cython 3.2.0b2, we're seeing new `-Wincompatible-pointer-types` build errors

```
    + meson setup /project /project/.mesonpy-aoo05_sp -Dbuildtype=release -Db_ndebug=if-release -Db_vscrt=md --vsenv --native-file=/project/.mesonpy-aoo05_sp/meson-python-native-file.ini

...

     FAILED: [code=1] pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/meson-generated_pandas__libs_tslibs_base.pyx.c.o
    cc -Ipandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p -Ipandas/_libs/tslibs -I../pandas/_libs/tslibs -I../../tmp/pip-build-env-_9vmpzyj/overlay/lib/python3.11/site-packages/numpy/_core/include -I../pandas/_libs/include -I/opt/_internal/cpython-3.11.14/include/python3.11 -fvisibility=hidden -fdiagnostics-color=always -DNDEBUG -D_FILE_OFFSET_BITS=64 -Wall -Winvalid-pch -Wextra -std=c11 -O3 -DNPY_NO_DEPRECATED_API=0 -DCYTHON_USE_TYPE_SPECS=1 -DNPY_TARGET_VERSION=NPY_1_21_API_VERSION -fPIC -MD -MQ pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/meson-generated_pandas__libs_tslibs_base.pyx.c.o -MF pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/meson-generated_pandas__libs_tslibs_base.pyx.c.o.d -o pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/meson-generated_pandas__libs_tslibs_base.pyx.c.o -c pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.pyx.c

    pandas/_libs/tslibs/ccalendar.cpython-311-x86_64-linux-gnu.so.p/pandas/_libs/tslibs/ccalendar.pyx.c:6421:70: error: passing argument 3 of ‘__Pyx_ImportFunction_3_2_0b2’ from incompatible pointer type [-Wincompatible-pointer-types]
     6421 |       if (__Pyx_ImportFunction_3_2_0b2(__pyx_t_1, __pyx_import_name, *__pyx_import_pointer, __pyx_import_current_signature) < (0)) __PYX_ERR(0, 1, __pyx_L1_error)

     2617 | static int __Pyx_ImportFunction_3_2_0b2(PyObject *module, const char *funcname, void (**f)(void), const char *sig);
          |   
```

A full log is available in our [cibuildwheel job](https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/actions/runs/18863344238/job/53826247322)

### Code to reproduce the behaviour:

The Cython files that are raising build errors are

https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/main/pandas/_libs/tslibs/base.pyx
https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/main/pandas/_libs/tslibs/ccalendar.pyx

### Expected behaviour

Compilation should pass `-Wincompatible-pointer-types`

### OS

Linux

### Python version

3.11, 3.12, 3.13, 3.14

### Cython version

3.2.0b2

### Additional context

_No response_

comment_data.body: Thanks for the report - this was fixed earlier today
Ah sorry for not looking at the closed issues and thanks for the quick fix!

title: [BUG?]: `__Pyx_modinit_shared_function_import_code` may fail `-Wincompatible-pointer-types` in 3.2.0b2
